AMSI EVASION BY CUSTOM SCRIPTING REVERSE SHELLS 

AMSI - Anti Malware Scanning Interface is an attempt by Microsoft to overcome the advantage held by interpreted scripts. These do not write to disk like .exe's and are executed in memory. 
Traditional AV's scan the files in disk for malicious signature. I simplest way to evade AMSI is to write your own scripts. 

